This term refers to a period of time 200 million to 146 million years ago marked by an abundance of dinosaurs as well as the first appearance of birds and mammals. It is one chapter of the Mesozoic era, which occurred between 252 and 66 million years ago and saw both the rise and extinction of dinosaurs. The Jurassic era gets its name from the Jura Mountains, which border France and Switzerland; the fossil-rich limestone formations of this mountain range were estimated to have taken shape in the aforementioned time period.|
